  <releasedate>2025-10-15</releasedate>
  <summary>&lt;p>&lt;b>Recommendations&lt;/b>&lt;br />&lt;br />1. For gtk app blur Effect you can use this extension &lt;b>kwin-effects-forceblur&lt;/b> &lt;a href="https://github.com/taj-ny/kwin-effects-forceblur">&lt;/a>&lt;a href="https://github.com/taj-ny/kwin-effects-forceblur">https://github.com/taj-ny/kwin-effects-forceblur&lt;/a>&lt;br />&lt;br />      Go to System Sttings &amp;gt; Window Management &amp;gt; Desktop Effects &amp;gt; Better Blur, turn it on !&lt;br />&lt;br />      Open Better Blur Configure window &amp;gt; Force blur active Blur all except matching&lt;br />&lt;br /> 2. For better looking please use this pack with Kvantum engine.&lt;br />&lt;br />      Run kvantummanager to choose and apply MacTahoe theme.&lt;br />&lt;br />3. Install &lt;b>MacTahoe icon theme&lt;/b> &lt;a href="https://github.com/vinceliuice/MacTahoe-icon-theme">&lt;/a>&lt;a href="https://github.com/vinceliuice/MacTahoe-icon-theme">https://github.com/vinceliuice/MacTahoe-icon-theme&lt;/a>&lt;br />     for a more consistent and beautiful experience.&lt;br />&lt;br />4. Install &lt;b>MacTahoe cursors theme&lt;/b> &lt;a href="https://github.com/vinceliuice/MacTahoe-icon-theme/tree/main/cursors">&lt;/a>&lt;a href="https://github.com/vinceliuice/MacTahoe-icon-theme/tree/main/cursors">https://github.com/vinceliuice/MacTahoe-icon-theme/tree/main/cursors&lt;/a>&lt;br />     for a more consistent and beautiful experience.&lt;/p></summary>
